
See README for more.

./setup-openbsd.sh [arch [vers [target dir]]]

- sets up a Qemu compatible VM in $HOME/Qemu/OpenBSD (or your target)
- arch can be amd64 (default), i386, sparc or sparc64

./run-openbsd.sh [arch [barf]]

- runs the VM at your convenience. arch is amd64 if not specified.
If you barf, you get a non-curses console.


